public class HealthInspector
extends com.google.common.util.concurrent.AbstractIdleService

Keeps track of the number of heartbeat records received from all SQL Compiler processes.

Constructor Detail

HealthInspector

public HealthInspector(ProcessMonitor processMonitor)
Constructor for HealthInspector which ensures the liveness of the SQL Compiler processes. If the class fails to detect a heartbeat from every registered process in the last two seconds then this class invokes the ProcessMonitor.notifyFailure(java.util.Set) defined in the ProcessMonitor object.

Parameters:
processMonitor - The reference of the class that implements ProcessMonitor.notifyFailure(java.util.Set)
Method Detail

register

public void register(String processName)
Registers the provided process name for health inspection. This function should be invoked for every process that has to be monitored by this class.

Parameters:
processName - The unique name of the process that is being registered for monitoring

ping

public void ping(String processName)
Logs the ping generated by the given process name. This function should be invoked for every ping that is received.

Parameters:
processName - Name of the pinging process

startUp

protected void startUp()
                throws Exception
This function initiates the monitoring services that checks if a heartbeat from each registered process was detected in the last 2 seconds. In case of failure, ProcessMonitor.notifyFailure(java.util.Set) of the constructor's parameter object is invoked.
